---

CRYPTOGRAPHIC COMPONENTS

The Software uses the following cryptographic primitives:

- SHA-256 for hash chain construction (hashlib — Python standard library)
- Ed25519 for digital signatures (PyNaCl — libsodium binding)
- Merkle trees for replay-verifiable state

These components are used as described in the Software's documentation.
Zorynex makes no warranty regarding the suitability of these components
for any particular regulatory requirement. Users are responsible for
validating compliance with applicable regulations including SR 11-7,
EU AI Act, and CFPB requirements in their specific jurisdiction.

